  "articleSummary": "Thearticle argues that an AI agent’s real value comes from its ability to interact with business systems, and that the “Model Context Protocol” (MCP) is the missing piece that turns a standalone chatbot into a fully integrated tool. It explains MCP as a universal integration layer—analogous to USB‑C—that lets agents access services like Salesforce, Google Maps, or weather APIs without writing custom wrappers for each, and shows how Mastra’s MCPClient handles both local and remote tool connections, per‑user authentication, and composite tool composition. The tone is a practical tutorial aimed at developers building production‑grade AI agents, using the recurring metaphor of “hands and eyes” (or cables) to frame the integration problem and its solution.",
